  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a randomized controlled trial with the aim of evaluating the effect of
      homebased inspiratory muscle training (IMT) for patients with COPD in Norway. The
      intervention group will train with threshold IMT for 6 weeks. The control group will not
      participate in any other training method or sham. Evaluation parameters are maximal
      inspiratory pressure, six minute walk test, COPD assessment test, modified Medical research
      council dyspnea scale and spirometry.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
